  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I get rid of a redirecting virus in Chrome and Opera on my Android?",
  "response": "Getting rid of a redirecting virus on Chrome and Opera on your Android can be challenging, but following these steps should help:\n\n1. **Check and Remove Suspicious Apps**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Apps/Applications**.\n   - Look for any unfamiliar or recently installed apps.\n   - Select the app and choose **Uninstall**.\n\n2. **Clear Browser Data**:\n   - Open **Chrome** or **Opera**.\n   - Tap the **three dots** (menu icon) in the top right corner.\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Privacy** > **Clear browsing data**.\n   - Select **All time** and check **Browsing history**, **Cookies and site data**, and **Cached images and files**.\n   - Tap **Clear data**.\n\n3. **Disable Extensions**:\n   - Open **Chrome** or **Opera**.\n   - Tap the **three dots** > **Settings** > **Extensions**.\n   - Disable or remove any suspicious extensions.\n\n4. **Scan for Malware**:\n   - Install a reputable antivirus app such as **Malwarebytes**, **Avast**, or **Bitdefender** from the Google Play Store.\n   - Run a full scan and follow the instructions to remove any threats.\n\n5. **Reset Browser Settings**:\n   - Open **Chrome** or **Opera**.\n   - Tap the **three dots** > **Settings**.\n   - Scroll down and tap **Advanced** (for Chrome) or **Site Settings** (for Opera).\n   - Tap **Restore settings to their original defaults** (Chrome) or **Reset settings** (Opera).\n\n6. **Update Your Browser**:\n   - Go to **Google Play Store**.\n   - Search for **Chrome** or **Opera**, check if an update is available, and update to the latest version.\n\n7. **Check Device Administrator Permissions**:\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Security** > **Device administrators**.\n   - Ensure that no suspicious apps have been granted these permissions. If you find any, disable them.\n\n8. **Reboot in Safe Mode**:\n   - Hold down the **power button** until the power off menu appears.\n   - Long-press **Power off** until a prompt to reboot into Safe Mode appears, then confirm.\n   - In Safe Mode, repeat steps to uninstall suspicious apps and run antivirus scans.\n\n9. **Factory Reset** (last resort):\n   - Backup your data first.\n   - Go to **Settings** > **System** > **Reset** > **Factory data reset**.\n   - Confirm and proceed with the reset. \n\nRemember, a factory reset will wipe all data on your device, so use this as a last resort if the other steps do not work.\n\nAfter completing these steps, the redirecting virus should be removed from your device.",
